## 📊 Key Results

### Q_crit — Standard vs DICE Latch
The DICE latch achieves **~5.6× higher Q_crit** (85 fC vs 15 fC), providing significantly better SEU immunity at the cost of 2.4× area.

### Window of Vulnerability
The standard latch is vulnerable for **~180ps** per clock cycle at 1 GHz. The DICE architecture reduces this to **~30ps** — an 83% reduction.

### Recommended Architecture
For space-grade applications: **DICE latch** — best balance of area overhead and single-node SEU immunity.  
For safety-critical automotive: **C-element latch** — lower area overhead, sufficient Q_crit for terrestrial environments.

